      "writtenOn": "2026-05-08T21:24:38Z",
      "side": 0,
      "message": "`openid` is enough for what this charm needs from Keystone. The only OIDC-specific config Keystone gets is `remote_id_attribute \u003d HTTP_OIDC_ISS`, and the `iss` claim is mandatory in every OIDC ID token. The `sub` claim is also mandatory. Anything beyond that (email, profile) is only relevant if an operator\u0027s mapping rules reference it.\n\nI confirmed this in a test deployment where the IdP advertises only [\"openid\"]: rendered `OIDCScope \"openid\"`, `apache2ctl -t` clean, and the flow no longer fails with invalid_scope.",
      "parentUuid": "65201936_69d43fed",
      "revId": "9dd0f186c1ffb4be1d940ab214238b69175f9d36",
